The Montana History Compass moved to the Montana Historical Society website!

Visit the new Montana History Compass to find our lists of Legislators in Montana. Our lists of Territorial and State Legislators and Women Elected Official still resides here until further notice.

Territorial and State Legislators

Click one of the links below for lists of legislators who served during Montana's territorial period from 1864 to 1889 and during Montana's statehood from 1889 to 1942. Or if you're looking for a particular legislator you can use the search box in the upper right hand corner of this Wiki page.

Women Elected Officials

Click the above heading for lists of women legislators, women delegates to the 1972 Constitutional Convention, and women elected to statewide office in Montana.
